From ecec22b0cf277404d8934290642f845e0fd0b8d6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Avula Sri Charan <asrichar@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 12 Jun 2025 08:09:38 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] QSDK:CP: Adevertise recovery Mode as Mode-0/Mode-1 to FW

By default FW will operate in Mode-0 recovery Mode which means
whenever there is a crash in Q6 the partner device crash indication
is sent to all the Q6 that are part of the MLO. But for Mode-1
recovery only the asserted readio should go for a Q6 restart.
To achieve this and to toggle between Mode-0 and Mode-1 recovery
modes FW rely on MLO global memory allocated during QMI seqeunce.

This will be used a Shared mem between FW and host to advertise
the recovery mode as Mode-0/Mode-1. Added changes to parse this MLO
memory and get the address of shared memory and poulate in ath12k_base.

Also add support to send the crash notification as userpd crash
for AHB/HYBRID chipsets.

Add support to trigger umac reset in case of Mode-1 recovery
and also for the cleanup of ML peer in non asserted partner
chipsets.

